Until recently, several states, among them Germany, were opposed to making these nominal documents available to the public, because of the sensitive nature of some information.
What are the presumed homosexuality or mental disability of some victims of deportation.
The registers of concentration camps or warrants put together by the Gestapo were collected after the war for the practical purpose of finding deported or forced labor subjected to civilian citizens, bringing them proof of their internment in order to open the way to their compensation.
Today, more than 300 permanent employees in Bad Arolsen are engaged in tens of thousands of individual applications.
