What insurance is right for me?
Car insurance that protects the driver in the event of an accident. represents a significant expense that depends on various factors, such as age, status, gender, the length of possession of the driver's license, the type of vehicle to be insured or used, etc.
Having a car is just the beginning.
Choosing the right car insurance is even more difficult than choosing a car model.
First of all, we need to clarify what we are talking about.
Car insurance is an agreement between the insurance company and the insured.
This obligation takes the form of an insurance contract, which stipulates that the insurance company receives an agreed insurance amount of a certain amount for taking charge of paying damages in the event of an insurance event.
Insurance premiums are the price of insurance, which is determined with regard to various factors, such as age, condition, gender, length of possession of a driver's license, the type of vehicle that is insured or used, etc.
Insurance companies set their prices based on statistics, so the greater the likelihood of a crash, the higher the insurance rate.
For this reason, both people over the age of 25 and women must pay lower premiums, as statistics show that they have a lower risk index due to their caution.
In the same way, on the basis of the checks, insurance companies concluded that persons living in marriage have fewer accidents than single drivers.
The way the vehicle is used will affect the frequency of journeys and thus the likelihood that it will have an accident.
The increase in the frequency of journeys increases the probability.
There are many variables that insurance companies consider when they determine the price of premiums.
Therefore, the driver must study the situation well in order to choose the insurance that best corresponds to his profile of the insured person.
We will show here the most important variables for choosing this or that type of insurance, which, in addition to complying with the type of insured person, will also be at a reasonable price.
People under the age of twenty-five encounter various disadvantages, such as little driving experience and a short possession of a driver's license when they want to arrange premiums at an affordable price.
Although the insurance against all risks is ideal for good coverage, there are also cheaper options.
The most cautious drivers can choose insurance against all risks with a discount of premiums to get insurance coverage of all risks, but at a more affordable price.
This kind of contract would presuppose the client's participation in the payment of the insured event.
"Part of the payment of the insurance claim provided by the client will be determined in advance when determining the price of the premium, which will be all the higher the lower the co-payment would be," explains Luis Noguera, chief executive of First Europe in Spain, an internet insurance intermediary.
Another option is insurance extended to other participants in the operation so that the client insures against damages caused to other persons, but not against damage to his own car.
In addition, he would be insured against theft, fire and loss of the vehicle.
Recommendations.
If you are under the age of twenty-five, try to be attentive and prevent accidents as much as possible, as this will affect your bonus and allow you to reduce premiums in the future.
The bonus is a reduction in the base rate that the insurance company has.
On the other hand, malus is an increase in the aforementioned basic rate.
"The bonus and malus will depend on the insurance company and its profits.
If the insurance company has had a good year, it will be able to afford to raise the bonus,” Noguera explains.
After crossing the twenty-five-year limit, drivers are easier to get insurance, because the client’s risk index decreases, thanks to the experience gained.
For this reason, it is most recommended to arrange insurance against all risks at a discount.
"Young people usually cannot take advantage of the experience gained in advance when there is a crash, and neither can they manage," the director of the European company in Spain assures, adding that most of the accidents occur in the second year of proceedings, when the "fear of a newcomer" has already been overcome.
However, if the client is married but does not yet have children, it is better to arrange insurance against all risks, if his economic situation allows.
Families with children are considered by insurance companies to be the clientele with the lowest risk index and therefore their premiums will be lower.
In this case, the best insurance would be insurance against all risks with a discount of insurance premiums (which could be 300 euros) or with a high bonus, insurance extended to other traffic participants, starting from the third year since the purchase of the vehicle.
"Their management is calmer and their purchasing capacity is higher, so they can afford the luxury of getting the highest discount," remarks Luis Noguera.
Pensioners are advised to insure against all risks with a discount of premiums (which is 150 euros) or insurance extended to other traffic participants if a high bonus has been achieved.
It must be said that car insurance is something important not only because it protects the driver in the event of a crash, but also because it represents a considerable expense, which is a good reason to properly study the insurance options that would suit us best in view of our personal situation.
